NOTE:<br><br>
I have posted the Orange County Register's article about the Viet Nam Traveling Memorial Wall, and it's debut in Little Saigon on Thread #49.<br><br>
For details sake, the Westminister Civic Center is a few blocks from the actual &quot;hub&quot; of Little Saigon, and is a sprawling complex of Courthouses and parking lots, county library, etc.<br><br>
Thought this might make it easier than my trying to summarize the &quot;details&quot; which I didn't know when I was there. The wall was at the Civic Center, and if you parked in between, Little Saigon and The Wall were all in walking distance.  (and a great and cheap Japanese Resturant too. No Betty, I didn't eat lyche nuts (ugh) but springs rolls and dim sum anytime)<br><br>
